				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text {SiO}_2$$\end{document} remains unchanged in this work. However, a mentionable characteristic of the used material system is their relatively high difference in the complex, dispersive refractive indices for wavelengths of the visible spectrum. Studying Table 1 implies that the MLTF decreases the total efficacy of a white LED corresponding to α=90∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
